{"title_page": "Farit Ismeth Emir", "text_new": "{{recentdeath}}\n{{infobox person\n| name= Farit Ismeth Emir\n| native_name= \u0641\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062a \u064a\u0633\u0645\u0649\u062b \u0627\u064a\u0645\u064a\u0631\n| birth_date = 26 October 1954\n| birth_place = [[Teluk Intan]], [[Perak Darul Ridzuan|Perak]], [[Federated Malay States]] {{small|(now [[Malaysia]])}}\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2020|4|20|1954|10|26}}<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal\">Farihad Shalla Mahmud (20 April 2020). [https://www.bharian.com.my/hiburan/selebriti/2020/04/679435/farit-ismeth-emir-meninggal-dunia Farit Ismeth Emir meninggal dunia] ''[[Berita Harian]]''. Achieved on 20 April 2020.</ref>\n| death_place = [[Petaling Jaya]], [[Selangor]], Malaysia\n| other_names = Pak Ngah<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal dunia\">Ridzuan Abdul Rahman (20 April 2020). [https://www.hmetro.com.my/utama/2020/04/568974/farit-ismeth-emir-meninggal-dunia Farit Ismeth Emir meninggal dunia] ''[[Harian Metro]]''. Dicapai pada 20 April 2020.</ref>\n| known_for = [[News anchor]] for [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]]\n| years_active = 1980\u20132020\n| children = 7 (including [[DJ Fuzz]])\n}}\n'''Farit Ismeth Emir''' (26 October 1954 - 20 April 2020)<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal\"/> was a Malaysian [[news anchor]], best known as a news anchor on [[Radio Television Malaysia]] (RTM) in ''Bes Dunia'' segment involving foreign affairs news. He once contributed his voice in [[Dunhill (cigarette)|Dunhill]]'s cigarette advertisement where his phrase, \"Gaya, mutu, keunggulan\" (Style, quality, excellence) was very popular during the time.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/lifestyle/entertainment/2020/04/20/newscaster-popular-for-voicing-the-gaya-mutu-keunggulan-ad-dies-at-66|language=en|accessdate=20 April 2020|date=20 April 2020|publisher=[[The Star Online]]|author=Kenneth Chaw|title=Voice of 'Gaya, Mutu, Keunggulan' ad, newscaster Farit Ismeth Emir, dies at 66}}</ref> He is married and has 7 children. His son, Farzwa De-Attahir Emir or [[DJ Fuzz]], a [[DJ]], musician and composer.<ref>Grace Chen (27 Mei 2014). [https://www.thestar.com.my/business/sme/2014/05/27/talking-well-pays-well-the-gift-of-the-gab-is-now-a-valuable-commodity/ Talking well pays well] ''[[The Star Online]]''. Achieved on 20 July 2014.</ref>\n\nHe has previously played a doctoral role in RTM's popular [[radio drama]], ''Nombor 5 Persiaran 1'' (Number 5 Tour 1).<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal dunia\"/> Emir died in 20 April, 2020 at Assunta Hospital in [[Petaling Jaya]] at the age of 65.<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:People from Perak]]\n[[Category:Television news anchors]]\n{{Malaysia-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{recentdeath}}\n{{infobox person\n| name= Farit Ismeth Emir\n| native_name= \u0641\u0627\u0631\u064a\u062a \u064a\u0633\u0645\u0649\u062b \u0627\u064a\u0645\u064a\u0631\n| birth_date = 26 October 1954\n| birth_place = [[Teluk Intan]], [[Perak Darul Ridzuan|Perak]], [[Federated Malay States]] {{small|(now [[Malaysia]])}}\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2020|4|20|1954|10|26}}<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal\">Farihad Shalla Mahmud (20 April 2020). [https://www.bharian.com.my/hiburan/selebriti/2020/04/679435/farit-ismeth-emir-meninggal-dunia Farit Ismeth Emir meninggal dunia] ''[[Berita Harian]]''. Achieved on 20 April 2020.</ref>\n| death_place = [[Petaling Jaya]], [[Selangor]], Malaysia\n| other_names = Pak Ngah<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal dunia\">Ridzuan Abdul Rahman (20 April 2020). [https://www.hmetro.com.my/utama/2020/04/568974/farit-ismeth-emir-meninggal-dunia Farit Ismeth Emir meninggal dunia] ''[[Harian Metro]]''. Dicapai pada 20 April 2020.</ref>\n| known_for = [[News anchor]] for [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]]\n| years_active = 1980\u20132020\n| children = 7 (including [[DJ Fuzz]])\n}}\n'''Farit Ismeth Emir''' (26 October 1954 - 20 April 2020)<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal\"/> was a Malaysian [[news anchor]], best known as a news anchor on [[Radio Television Malaysia]] (RTM) in ''Bes Dunia'' segment involving foreign affairs news. He once contributed his voice in [[Dunhill (cigarette)|Dunhill]]'s cigarette advertisement where his phrase, \"Gaya, mutu, keunggulan\" (Style, quality, excellence) was very popular during the time.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/lifestyle/entertainment/2020/04/20/newscaster-popular-for-voicing-the-gaya-mutu-keunggulan-ad-dies-at-66|language=en|accessdate=20 April 2020|date=20 April 2020|publisher=[[The Star Online]]|author=Kenneth Chaw|title=Voice of 'Gaya, Mutu, Keunggulan' ad, newscaster Farit Ismeth Emir, dies at 66}}</ref> He is married and has 7 children. His son, Farzwa De-Attahir Emir or [[DJ Fuzz]], a [[DJ]], musician and composer.<ref>Grace Chen (27 Mei 2014). [https://www.thestar.com.my/business/sme/2014/05/27/talking-well-pays-well-the-gift-of-the-gab-is-now-a-valuable-commodity/ Talking well pays well] ''[[The Star Online]]''. Achieved on 20 July 2014.</ref>\n\nHe has previously played a doctoral role in RTM's popular [[radio drama]], ''Nombor 5 Persiaran 1'' (Number 5 Tour 1).<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal dunia\"/> Emir died in April 20, 2020 at Assunta Hospital in Petaling Jaya at the age of 66.<ref name=\"Farit Ismeth meninggal\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1954 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Malaysian people of Malay descent]]\n[[Category:Malaysian Muslims]]\n[[Category:People from Perak]]\n[[Category:Television news anchors]]\n{{Malaysia-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ricky250", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farit_Ismeth_Emir"}
