recoveries and 47 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 18 April reports\" />\n*Turkey has reported 3,783 new cases, bringing the total to 82,239. 121 have died, bringing the death toll to 1,890. Turkey has reported 1,822 recoveries and 40,520 tests.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 18 April reports\" />\n*Ukraine reports 444 new cases and 8 new deaths, bringing the total numbers to 5,106 and 133 respectively; a total of 275 patients have recovered.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0412 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0456 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0456\u043a\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043e 5106 \u0432\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0456\u0432 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0456\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u0445\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 COVID-19 |url=https://www.facebook.com/moz.ukr/posts/1512275935602173 |website=facebook.com |publisher=Ministry of Healthcare of Ukraine |accessdate=18 April 2020 |language=uk |date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n*The United Kingdom reports 888 deaths in hospitals, bringing the death toll to 15,464. UK authorities have tested 357,023 people, with 114,217 testing positive.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 18 April reports\" />\n*In the United States, the death toll has exceeded 31,000. New York state authorities have reported 540 deaths and over 2,000 hospital admissions in the last 24 hours.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 18 April reports\" /> \n*According to [[Johns Hopkins University]], the number of global cases has reached 2.3&nbsp;million while the global death toll has exceeded 159,000.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 18 April reports\" />\n\n===19 April===\n*The Africa Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC) has reported 55 new deaths, bringing the death toll to 1,080. The continent has reported 1,047 new cases, bringing the total number of infections to 21,317.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\">{{cite news |last1=Rashid |first1=Zaheena |last2=Alsaafin |first2=Linah |last3=Gadzo |first3=Mersiha |title=Protests over coronavirus lockdowns in US, Brazil: Live updates |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/protests-coronavirus-lockdowns-brazil-live-updates-200418233435533.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=19 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419224404/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/protests-coronavirus-lockdowns-brazil-live-updates-200418233435533.html |archive-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Canada has reported a total of 1,506 deaths and 33,922 cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Chile has reported a total of over 10,000 cases and 133 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*China has reported 16 new cases (including nine imported cases), bringing the total to 82,735.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Germany has reported 2,458 new cases, bringing the total to 139,897. Germany also reports 184 new deaths, bringing the total to 4,294.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*France has reported 395 deaths, bringing the death toll to 19,718. 5,744 remain in intensive care.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Guinea has reported 518 cases and five deaths. The deceased include several senior government officials including secretary-general Sekou Kourouma.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" /> \n*Honduras has reported a total of 472 cases and 46 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Indonesia has reported 327 new cases, bringing the total to 6,575. Indonesian health authorities also report 47 new deaths, bringing the total to 582.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" /> \n*Israel has reported 97 new cases, bringing the total to 13,362, with 156 being in critical condition. Israel has also reported 7 deaths, bringing the death toll to 171.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Italy has reported 433 new deaths and 3,047 new cases.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Japan has reported 568 new cases, bringing the total to 10,361. If combined with the 712 cases reported on a cruise ship quarantined near Tokyo, the total figure rises to 11,073. Japan has also reported a total of 174 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*Malaysia has reported 84 new cases, bringing the total to 5,389. Malaysian health authorities have also reported 95 recoveries, bringing the total to 3,197. Malaysia also reports one new death, bringing the death toll to 89.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tang |first1=Ashley |title=Covid-19: 84 new cases, 95 recovered, death toll now at 89 |url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/19/covid-19-84-new-cases-death-toll-now-at-89#cxrecs_s |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |date=19 April 2020 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20200419111106/https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2020/04/19/covid-19-84-new-cases-death-toll-now-at-89 |archivedate=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n*Mexico has reported a total of 7,947 cases and 650 deaths.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" />\n*The Netherlands has reported 1,066 new cases, bringing the total to 32,655. Dutch authorities have also confirmed 83 deaths, bringing the death toll to 3,684.<ref name=\"Al Jazeera 19 April reports\" /> \n*New Zealand has reported 9 new cases (4 confirmed and 5 probable), bringing the total to 1,431 (1,098 confirmed and 333 probable). Health authorities have also reported 45 new recoveries, bringing the total to 912. In addition, authorities confirm one death from the coronavirus during a post-morterm, bringing the total death toll to 12.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|title=COVID-19 \u2013 current cases|website=Health.govt.nz|date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419012032/https://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/diseases-and-conditions/covid-19-novel-coronavirus/covid-19-current-situation/covid-19-current-cases|archive-date=19 April 2